%N A134351 Binomial transform of [1, 5, -1, 5, -1, 5, ...]. Inverse binomial transform of A134350.
%H A134351 Andrew Howroyd, <a href="/A134351/b134351.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1000</a>
%H A134351 <a href="/index/Rec#order_02">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (3,-2).
%F A134351 a(n) = 2 + 2^(n+1) for n >= 1; a(0)=1. - _Emeric Deutsch_, Oct 24 2007
%F A134351 O.g.f.: (-1-3*x+6*x^2)/((1-x)*(-1+2*x)). - _R. J. Mathar_, Apr 02 2008
%F A134351 From _Elmo R. Oliveira_, Jul 06 2026: (Start)
%F A134351 E.g.f.: 2*exp(x)*(1 + exp(x)) - 3.
%F A134351 a(n) = 2*A048578(n-1) for n > 0.
%F A134351 a(n) = 3*a(n-1) - 2*a(n-2) for n > 2. (End)
%e A134351 a(3) = 18 = (1, 3, 3, 1) dot (1, 5, -1, 5) = (1 + 15 - 3 + 5).
%p A134351 1,seq(2^(n+1)+2,n=1..25); # _Emeric Deutsch_, Oct 24 2007
%o A134351 (PARI) a(n) = if(n==0, 1, 2 + 2^(n+1)) \\ _Andrew Howroyd_, Sep 14 2025
